Business Brief -- Plum Creek Timber Co.:
   Company Posts Profit Rise
   Of 41% for Fourth Quarter
Plum Creek's profit improved despite a dip in revenue
because of robust prices in the period for its wood products
for repair and remodeling jobs.
   For the year, Plum Creek, hurt by the recession like other
wood-products companies, earned $18.7 million, or $1.10 a
unit, down 16% from year-ago profit of $22.2 million, or
$1.33 a unit. Revenue increased 4.6% to $389.8 million from
$372.8 million.
   Plum Creek said its results for the first half of 1992
will "continue to be impacted by the sluggish economy."
   In late trading on the New York Stock Exchange, Plum Creek
units were quoted at $34.875, up 50 cents.